	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Sir&#33;</p>
				<p>You can <sic>precive</sic><add>&#63;</add>&#44; <add>&#63;</add> these few lines<lb/> that some of the subscribers&#44;<lb/> have much to say about the prices<lb/> of the Books&#44; and in particular<lb/> <persName>Moses Gitzky</persName> the <add>&#63;</add>.<lb/> <persName>E. J. Bernheim</persName>&#44; will not take one&#44; on<lb/> account&#44; he wants a complete Bible<lb/> <sic>wit</sic> English&#44; and <add>Hebrew</add> for a few Dollars.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please to <sic>ansere</sic></p>
			<pb n="3"/>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><placeName>Buffalo</placeName>&#44; <date>Wednesday 12th Iyar 5614</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><date>May 19</date></p>
				<p>in poor imitat<lb/> of German</p>
				<p>Peace etc. to the Master&#44; Sweet Singer of <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#44; <persName>Isaac</persName>&#8212;</p>
				<p>Most honored friend.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I herewith notify you that the books have happily arrived<lb/> I have looked carefully into the account&#44; but I regret<lb/> to notify you that many of the subscribers are not<lb/> from this place&#44; as I have already written to you.  I<lb/> shall gladly take them over&#44; though I have very few<lb/> pupils.  Your account amounts to &#36;71.&#8212;&#44; but my<lb/> order was simply &#36;41.&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Madam Gostzky</persName> told me&#44; and gave me her<lb/> advertisement which is here enclosed&#44; as you<lb/> see.  You know that <persName>Mr. Asser Friedenberg</persName> does<lb/> not pay anyone.  He will take a copy&#8212;free. I<lb/> however&#44; will not deliver a single Testament<lb/> unless I receive payment for it.  As soon as<lb/> I have collected the money&#44; you can depend<lb/> upon my word&#44; I shall send it to you by<lb/> express.  The box has not been opened yet&#44; and<lb/> I shall wait till I get word from you what<lb/> to do with the superfluous books&#44; in cases</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>where the subscribers do not reside here.<lb/>  Have the goodness to reply to me by return<lb/> mail.  Also kindly print&#42; for me another copy<lb/> of the Testament and also of the Prayer&#45;book<lb/>  The first copies were <del>taken</del> stolen from me.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please reply&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Respectfully etc</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">Isaac M. Slatkin</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Slatkin</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>23 Commercial St.</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Buffalo&#44; N. Y.</placeName></p>
				<p>I suppose he means name on the cover</p>
				<p rend="The following lines are written sideways at the left side of the page"></p>
				<p>P.S. It is possible that I shall pay<lb/> you a visit this summer.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr Joseph Ash</persName>&#44; &#38; family</p>
		</body>
